    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I've spent some time analyzing this one, thinking and experimenting re: how `task_runner` or some other approach could be used in the existing codebase to get the work in `addContact` off the main (UI) thread:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/blob/master/src/app/profile/views/contacts.nim#L200\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-lib/blob/master/status/contacts.nim#L94-L123\r\n\r\nThe difficulty is that, per the code in the second link above, adding a contact involves reads and writes to the model data that lives on the main thread, interleaved with calls to status-go, and emission of EventEmitter events.\r\n\r\nSo it's all interwoven synchronous calls on the main thread (the UI thread). Model data access (read or write) *must* be done on the thread hosting the model because of constraints of Nim v1.2's memory model. The same is true for usage of EventEmitter. Finally, since the work is done in the context of (recently) split-off status-lib, we don't have a ready way to signal back from `task_runner` if we attempted to move the status-go calls to a `task_runner` worker or pool, i.e. in status-desktop we rely on Qt slot/signal to pass task results back to the main thread but that's not available in the context of status-lib.\r\n\r\nHopefully ðŸ¤ž, the changes that will be made re: #3651 will improve the performance and reduce or effectively eliminate the UI freeze when adding a contact.",
